\SE[2]...I wonder what kind of crimes the people trapped
here have committed?

\SE[2]This section mainly consists of political prisoners.
\SE[3]Embezzlement, bribery, illegal donations, and various
other things...

\SE[2]It means stealing money from the country without
permission... \!\SE[3]And also accepting money that you
shouldn't receive from others.

\SE[2]I had heard about such incidents, but I didn't know
there were so many political prisoners...

\SE[51]...Fortunately, the security here is lighter compared
to the section for violent crimes. \SE[3] Our destination is
right there. Let's go.

I... opposed the land development a little. And then, before
I knew it, I ended up in a place like this...
\SE[10]I wonder if this person really did something bad...?

\SE[2]Everyone who gets caught says the same thing, don't
they?
\SE[2]...Don't innocent people say the same thing too?
Prisoner who wants to go home
I want to go home quickly... I have a wife and children...

\SE[53] (There are many people in this section who are in
serious situations...)

Oh my, I'm really in trouble.... My life was on the fast
track to success... and now it's all over.... Just because I
joined the moderate faction....

Hey, you... What month and day is it today? I've lost track
of time...

Hey, you... If you don't mind, could you kill me? Waiting to
die here... I can't bear it.
\SE[51]...There's nothing we can do right now.

I really haven't done anything.... I didn't steal the money
from the safe....
